text: The 1965 World Table Tennis Championships – Women's Singles was the 28th edition of the women's singles championship. Naoko Fukatsu defeated Lin Hui- ching in the final by three sets to two, to win the title. ==Seeds== # Maria Alexandru # Ella Constantinescu # Masako Seki # Noriko Yamanaka # Han Ju-chen # Naoko Fukatsu # Lin Hui-ching # Éva Kóczián-Földy # Liang Li-chen # Mary Shannon # Li Ho-nan # Ti Chiang-hua # Erzsebet Jurik # Diane Rowe # L'i Li-fen # Cheng Min-chih # Zoja Rudnova # Edit Buchholz # Svetlana Grinberg ==Results== ==See also== List of World Table Tennis Championships medalists ==References== \- Category:1965 in women's table tennis
